    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-02-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-02-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="81"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                <head>No. 387.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName corresp="#p_DES1" type="from"
                            >Sickles</persName> to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HF1" type="to"
                            >Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Received Feb. 14—10 a.m.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-02-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 12, 1873</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <persName>Castelar</persName> said to me to-night, with much feeling, that the
                    Spanish Republic looked especially to our Government and people for sympathy and
                    support, and inquired with solicitude whether our recognition would be
                    delayed.</p>
                <p>President and cabinet entered on their duties at quarter past 2 this morning.
                    Cortes adjourned till this afternoon.</p>
                <p>Madrid is illuminated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DES1">SICKLES</persName>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
